  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting communities affected by HIV and TB in Zambia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Zambia has one of the world&#x2019;s highest HIV rates with one in seven adults living with the virus. About half of people with HIV also have tuberculosis, but many of them don&#x2019;t realise they have both. Tuberculosis is responsible for more than a quarter of all HIV-related deaths in Zambia. This project will work with the government to get people with these diseases to health centres, so they can be properly treated. Volunteers will teach people to recognise the symptoms of HIV and tuberculosis, and encourage them to get medical help. People with these diseases will be visited at home to encourage them to stick with their treatment. Members of their family will be trained so they can care for them properly. As a result, more people will get better quality treatment for HIV and tuberculosis.</narrative>
  </description>
